SUMMARY:M: Axel commented he was a stressed because he ran out of time on his English oral CAT
DESCRIPTION:Axel said he felt stressed because he had 48 seconds to finish his English CAT oral today. This was the second class of a two part class on this task. The first part had been on the mo day. He commented that on the Monday he barely did any work because he couldn’t focus. ( I noted on the Wednesday Axel had come home for the third cycle in a row with four days worth of his ADHD medication still not taken from his five days with his dad) \nHad Axel have taken his medication he may have had a very different outcome on the Friday class.
